      {
         "id": "SECTION_prerequisites",
         "text": [
            {
               "text": "<p><span id=\"htZoomImageMsg\"></span></p><p><span id=\"htChartMsg\"></span></p><p><span id=\"htAgeMsg\"></span></p><p><span id=\"htAmericaAbyaYalaMsg\"></span> (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('160fb48c-1711-491e-a1aa-e1257e7889af'); return false;\">Porto-Gonçalves, Carlos Walter, <htdate0>, pp. 39-43</a>).</p>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": [
                  {
                     "type": "gregory",
                     "year": "2011",
                     "month": "",
                     "day": ""
                  }
               ],
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "### Prerequisites\n\nAlthough this is the first text in Volume 2 of the First Steps section, it requires knowledge already studied throughout the entirety of Volume 1 (<htcite0>). Therefore, we recommend studying Volume 1 before proceeding.",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "b5efc8f9-c268-430f-9681-7a43848ee48e",
                     "text": "History Tracers Team",
                     "page": "First Steps",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2024",
                        "month": "",
                        "day": ""
                     }
                  }
               ],
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ""
            }
         ]
      },
      {
         "id": "SECTION_introduction",
         "text": [
            {
               "text": "### Introduction\n\nObserve **Graph 1** below:",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p class=\"desc\"><svg width=\"450\" height=\"140\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"black\"> <defs> <marker id=\"arrow\" viewBox=\"0 0 10 10\" refX=\"5\" refY=\"5\" markerWidth=\"6\" markerHeight=\"6\" orient=\"auto-start-reverse\"> <path d=\"M 0 0 L 10 5 L 0 10 z\" /></marker> </defs> <line x1=\"2\" y1=\"110\" x2=\"440\" y2=\"110\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" marker-end=\"url(#arrow)\" /> <text x=\"0\" y=\"135\" font-size=\"1.5em\">0</text> <text x=\"41\" y=\"135\" font-size=\"1.5em\">1</text> <text x=\"82\" y=\"135\" font-size=\"1.5em\">2</text> <text x=\"123\" y=\"135\" font-size=\"1.5em\">3</text> <text x=\"164\" y=\"135\" font-size=\"1.5em\">4</text> <text x=\"205\" y=\"135\" font-size=\"1.5em\">5</text> <text x=\"246\" y=\"135\" font-size=\"1.5em\">6</text> <text x=\"287\" y=\"135\" font-size=\"1.5em\">7</text> <text x=\"328\" y=\"135\" font-size=\"1.5em\">8</text> <text x=\"369\" y=\"135\" font-size=\"1.5em\">9</text> <text x=\"405\" y=\"135\" font-size=\"1.5em\">10</text> <line x1=\"3\" y1=\"110\" x2=\"3\" y2=\"120\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <line x1=\"44\" y1=\"110\" x2=\"44\" y2=\"120\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <line x1=\"85\" y1=\"110\" x2=\"85\" y2=\"120\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <line x1=\"126\" y1=\"110\" x2=\"126\" y2=\"120\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <line x1=\"167\" y1=\"110\" x2=\"167\" y2=\"120\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <line x1=\"208\" y1=\"110\" x2=\"208\" y2=\"120\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <line x1=\"249\" y1=\"110\" x2=\"249\" y2=\"120\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <line x1=\"290\" y1=\"110\" x2=\"290\" y2=\"120\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <line x1=\"331\" y1=\"110\" x2=\"331\" y2=\"120\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <line x1=\"372\" y1=\"110\" x2=\"372\" y2=\"120\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <line x1=\"413\" y1=\"110\" x2=\"413\" y2=\"120\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> </svg></p><p class=\"desc\"><b>Graph 1</b>: Representation of a path.</p>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "Now, compare it with **Figure 1**, which presents a utensil used in the kitchen of the Shona culture (<htcite0>).",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "cc162709-bdc3-469b-a208-e900f4570842",
                     "text": "Sadomba, Zvakanyorwa Wilbert",
                     "page": "",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2024",
                        "month": "",
                        "day": ""
                     }
                  }
               ],
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p class=\"desc\"><img id=\"z0\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('z0', '0%')\" src=\"images/Zimbabue/Gourd.png\" class=\"imgcenter\"/><b>Figure 1</b>: Gourd in a Zimbabwean cooking pot. Photo used with permission from Dr. Zvakanyorwa Wilbert Sadomba.</p>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<center><div class=\"first_steps_reflection_parent\"><div class=\"first_steps_reflection question_mark\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-brain\"></i></div><div class=\"first_steps_reflection\"><b>Reflection 1: Something is missing</b><br /><br /><b>Chart 1</b> shows numbers scattered along a line, while <b>Figure 1</b> presents a kitchen object that is closed on its sides.<br /><br />How can we use the numbers to close the holes in <b>Graph 1</b>?</div></div></center>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            }
         ]
      },
      {
         "id": "SECTION_first_idea",
         "text": [
            {
               "text": "### A First Step\n\nTo better understand our needs, we will use geometric figures that help us better understand what we want to do. First, we will draw a rectangle with the length of the line in **Graph 1**.",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p class=\"desc\"><svg width=\"450\" height=\"140\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"black\"> <defs> <marker id=\"arrow\" viewBox=\"0 0 10 10\" refX=\"5\" refY=\"5\" markerWidth=\"6\" markerHeight=\"6\" orient=\"auto-start-reverse\"> <path d=\"M 0 0 L 10 5 L 0 10 z\" /></marker> </defs> <line x1=\"2\" y1=\"110\" x2=\"440\" y2=\"110\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" marker-end=\"url(#arrow)\" /> <text x=\"0\" y=\"135\" font-size=\"1.5em\">0</text> <text x=\"41\" y=\"135\" font-size=\"1.5em\">1</text> <text x=\"82\" y=\"135\" font-size=\"1.5em\">2</text> <text x=\"123\" y=\"135\" font-size=\"1.5em\">3</text> <text x=\"164\" y=\"135\" font-size=\"1.5em\">4</text> <text x=\"205\" y=\"135\" font-size=\"1.5em\">5</text> <text x=\"246\" y=\"135\" font-size=\"1.5em\">6</text> <text x=\"287\" y=\"135\" font-size=\"1.5em\">7</text> <text x=\"328\" y=\"135\" font-size=\"1.5em\">8</text> <text x=\"369\" y=\"135\" font-size=\"1.5em\">9</text> <text x=\"405\" y=\"135\" font-size=\"1.5em\">10</text> <line x1=\"3\" y1=\"110\" x2=\"3\" y2=\"120\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <line x1=\"44\" y1=\"110\" x2=\"44\" y2=\"120\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <line x1=\"85\" y1=\"110\" x2=\"85\" y2=\"120\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <line x1=\"126\" y1=\"110\" x2=\"126\" y2=\"120\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <line x1=\"167\" y1=\"110\" x2=\"167\" y2=\"120\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <line x1=\"208\" y1=\"110\" x2=\"208\" y2=\"120\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <line x1=\"249\" y1=\"110\" x2=\"249\" y2=\"120\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <line x1=\"290\" y1=\"110\" x2=\"290\" y2=\"120\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <line x1=\"331\" y1=\"110\" x2=\"331\" y2=\"120\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <line x1=\"372\" y1=\"110\" x2=\"372\" y2=\"120\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <line x1=\"413\" y1=\"110\" x2=\"413\" y2=\"120\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <rect x=\"2\" y=\"2\" width=\"408\" height=\"95\" fill=\"lightblue\" stroke-width=\"1\"/></svg></p><p class=\"desc\"><b>Graph 2</b>: Representation of a rectangle on a trajectory.</p>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "The rectangle over the numbers does not solve our initial problem, but it can lead us to conclusions that do solve it.",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<center><div class=\"first_steps_reflection_parent\"><div class=\"first_steps_reflection question_mark\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-brain\"></i></div><div class=\"first_steps_reflection\"><b>Reflection 2: Filling ...</b><br /><br />Looking at <b>Graph 2</b>, how would you use a rectangle (or rectangles) to solve our space problem?</div></div></center>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            }
         ]
      },
      {
         "id": "SECTION_next_step",
         "text": [
            {
               "text": "### Fractionating Again\n\nThe rectangle that spans the width of all the numbers in **Graph 2** does not solve our problem of filling in the values between the numbers because it is larger than any interval between them.\n\nIf a whole rectangle does not solve the filling problem, our solution is to repeat what the universe accomplished and fractionate the whole (<htcite0>; <htcite1>). Let's begin by observing our hands (**Figure 2**):",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "112e532d-e8af-40d6-b1b5-527978ee42f3",
                     "text": "History Tracers Team",
                     "page": "Two Sides",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2025",
                        "month": "-1",
                        "day": "-1"
                     }
                  },
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "b6f9bd52-c0cb-497e-9217-1f9677d5b491",
                     "text": "History Tracers Team",
                     "page": "Expanding...",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2025",
                        "month": "",
                        "day": ""
                     }
                  }
               ],
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p><table class=\"book_navigation\"><tr><td>Left hand</td><td>Right hand</td></tr><tr><td><img id=\"imgLH\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgLH', '0%')\" src=\"images/HistoryTracers/Left_Hand.png\" class=\"imgcenter\"/></td><td><img id=\"imgRH\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgRH', '0%')\" src=\"images/HistoryTracers/Right_Hand.png\" class=\"imgcenter\"/></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\"><b>Figure 2</b>: Hands reprsentation. The source codes are available in project GitHub (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('240800f3-ede4-4deb-9d4e-915a3a03fa68'); return false;\">History Tracers Team, <htdate0>, Source code</a>)</td></tr></table></p>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": [
                  {
                     "type": "gregory",
                     "year": "2024",
                     "month": "-1",
                     "day": "-1"
                  }
               ],
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "The figure shows a person's two hands raised with all fingers extended.",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "Now, comparing the hands (**Figure 2**) with **Graphs 1 and 2**, we can conclude that our fingers have exactly the same number of spaces, even though there are 11 numbers in the graphs. This can be confirmed by subtracting each number from the previous one in **Chart 1**:",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p><math display=\"block\"> <mn>1</mn> <mo>-</mo> <mn>0</mn> <mo>=</mo> <mn>1</mn> </math></p><p><math display=\"block\"> <mn>2</mn> <mo>-</mo> <mn>1</mn> <mo>=</mo> <mn>1</mn> </math></p><p><math display=\"block\"> <mn>3</mn> <mo>-</mo> <mn>2</mn> <mo>=</mo> <mn>1</mn> </math></p><p><math display=\"block\"> <mn>4</mn> <mo>-</mo> <mn>3</mn> <mo>=</mo> <mn>1</mn> </math></p><p><math display=\"block\"> <mn>5</mn> <mo>-</mo> <mn>4</mn> <mo>=</mo> <mn>1</mn> </math></p><p><math display=\"block\"> <mn>6</mn> <mo>-</mo> <mn>5</mn> <mo>=</mo> <mn>1</mn> </math></p><p><math display=\"block\"> <mn>7</mn> <mo>-</mo> <mn>6</mn> <mo>=</mo> <mn>1</mn> </math></p><p><math display=\"block\"> <mn>8</mn> <mo>-</mo> <mn>7</mn> <mo>=</mo> <mn>1</mn> </math></p><p><math display=\"block\"> <mn>9</mn> <mo>-</mo> <mn>8</mn> <mo>=</mo> <mn>1</mn> </math></p><p><math display=\"block\"> <mn>10</mn> <mo>-</mo> <mn>9</mn> <mo>=</mo> <mn>1</mn> </math></p><p class=\"desc\"><b>Calculation 1</b>: Measuring the spaces between the numbers.</p>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "Next, we add all the results. Since they all have the same value, we don't need to add them one by one; instead, we can multiply the total number of results by 1 (<htcite0>):",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "eaa59295-fb80-4c33-b1e4-bcdf3c11dabf",
                     "text": "History Tracers Team",
                     "page": "Adding the Same Numbers",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2025",
                        "month": "5",
                        "day": "9"
                     }
                  }
               ],
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p><math display=\"block\"> <mn>10</mn> <mo>×</mo> <mn>1</mn> <mo>=</mo> <mn>10</mn> </math></p><p class=\"desc\"><b>Calculation 2</b>: Counting the number of spaces in <b>Graph 1</b>.</p>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "Given this scenario, let's divide the rectangle from **Graph 2** into 10 rectangles of the same height, with a width of length 1:",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p class=\"desc\"><svg width=\"450\" height=\"140\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"black\"> <defs> <marker id=\"arrow\" viewBox=\"0 0 10 10\" refX=\"5\" refY=\"5\" markerWidth=\"6\" markerHeight=\"6\" orient=\"auto-start-reverse\"> <path d=\"M 0 0 L 10 5 L 0 10 z\" /></marker> </defs> <line x1=\"2\" y1=\"110\" x2=\"440\" y2=\"110\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" marker-end=\"url(#arrow)\" /> <text x=\"0\" y=\"135\" font-size=\"1.5em\">0</text> <text x=\"41\" y=\"135\" font-size=\"1.5em\">1</text> <text x=\"82\" y=\"135\" font-size=\"1.5em\">2</text> <text x=\"123\" y=\"135\" font-size=\"1.5em\">3</text> <text x=\"164\" y=\"135\" font-size=\"1.5em\">4</text> <text x=\"205\" y=\"135\" font-size=\"1.5em\">5</text> <text x=\"246\" y=\"135\" font-size=\"1.5em\">6</text> <text x=\"287\" y=\"135\" font-size=\"1.5em\">7</text> <text x=\"328\" y=\"135\" font-size=\"1.5em\">8</text> <text x=\"369\" y=\"135\" font-size=\"1.5em\">9</text> <text x=\"405\" y=\"135\" font-size=\"1.5em\">10</text> <line x1=\"3\" y1=\"110\" x2=\"3\" y2=\"120\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <line x1=\"44\" y1=\"110\" x2=\"44\" y2=\"120\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <line x1=\"85\" y1=\"110\" x2=\"85\" y2=\"120\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <line x1=\"126\" y1=\"110\" x2=\"126\" y2=\"120\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <line x1=\"167\" y1=\"110\" x2=\"167\" y2=\"120\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <line x1=\"208\" y1=\"110\" x2=\"208\" y2=\"120\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <line x1=\"249\" y1=\"110\" x2=\"249\" y2=\"120\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <line x1=\"290\" y1=\"110\" x2=\"290\" y2=\"120\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <line x1=\"331\" y1=\"110\" x2=\"331\" y2=\"120\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <line x1=\"372\" y1=\"110\" x2=\"372\" y2=\"120\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <line x1=\"413\" y1=\"110\" x2=\"413\" y2=\"120\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"3\" /> <rect x=\"2\" y=\"2\" width=\"40\" height=\"95\" fill=\"lightblue\" stroke-width=\"1\"/> <rect x=\"43\" y=\"2\" width=\"40\" height=\"95\" fill=\"lightblue\" stroke-width=\"1\"/>  <rect x=\"84\" y=\"2\" width=\"40\" height=\"95\" fill=\"lightblue\" stroke-width=\"1\"/>  <rect x=\"125\" y=\"2\" width=\"40\" height=\"95\" fill=\"lightblue\" stroke-width=\"1\"/>  <rect x=\"166\" y=\"2\" width=\"40\" height=\"95\" fill=\"lightblue\" stroke-width=\"1\"/> <rect x=\"207\" y=\"2\" width=\"40\" height=\"95\" fill=\"lightblue\" stroke-width=\"1\"/> <rect x=\"248\" y=\"2\" width=\"40\" height=\"95\" fill=\"lightblue\" stroke-width=\"1\"/> <rect x=\"289\" y=\"2\" width=\"40\" height=\"95\" fill=\"lightblue\" stroke-width=\"1\"/> <rect x=\"330\" y=\"2\" width=\"40\" height=\"95\" fill=\"lightblue\" stroke-width=\"1\"/> <rect x=\"370\" y=\"2\" width=\"40\" height=\"95\" fill=\"lightblue\" stroke-width=\"1\"/></svg></p><p class=\"desc\"><b>Graph 3</b>: Representation of 10 rectangles along a path.</p>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<center><div class=\"first_steps_reflection_parent\"><div class=\"first_steps_reflection question_mark\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-brain\"></i></div><div class=\"first_steps_reflection\"><b>Reflection 3: Almost There</b><br /><br />What we have seen so far shows that <b>Graph 3</b>, although not the complete solution, gives us a first step toward better understanding the results between the numbers.<br /><br />Using the idea of rectangles and the operation of division, how would you fill the space between 0 and 1 with numbers?</div></div></center>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            }
         ]
      }
   ],
   "exercise_v2": [
      {
         "question": "Para medir o comprimento de algo, colocamos o zero em um extremo, e vemos o tamanho que ele possuí no outro extremo de um caminho com marcações númericas?",
         "yesNoAnswer": "Yes",
         "additionalInfo": "Conforme pode ser observado no Gráfico 2, o retângulo possuí exatamente a largura 10. Isto é reforçado pelos Cálculos 1 e 2 que confirmam este comprimento."
      }
   ],
